X: 21
T: Of The Father's Love Begotten
T: (SSAATTBB arrangement)
C: Words: Aurelius Prudentius Clemens, 5th Century.
C: Verses 1, 4-8 translated by John Mason Neale, 1854. Verses 2-3, 9 translated by Henry Williams Baker, 1859.
C: Music: 'Divinum Mysterium' or 'Corde Natus' Latin Plainsong, 13th Century.
C: Setting: "The Church Hymnal, Revised and Enlarged" (Episcopal), 1892, alt.
C: SSAATTBB arrangement: public domain source.
M: none
L: 1/4
Q: 1/4=108
%%staves [(1 2) (3 4) (5 6) (7 8)]
V:1 name="Soprano I"  clef=treble
V:2 name="Soprano II" clef=treble
V:3 name="Alto I"     clef=treble
V:4 name="Alto II"    clef=treble
V:5 name="Tenor I"    clef=treble middle=B3 transpose=-12
V:6 name="Tenor II"   clef=treble middle=B3 transpose=-12
V:7 name="Baritone"   clef=bass
V:8 name="Bass I"     clef=bass
K: F
%
% Key: F major (1 flat = Bb). No transposition from original — valid for lever harp.
% ABC pitch reference (K:F, standard ABC octave notation):
%   Treble clef: C=C4 D=D4 E=E4 F=F4 G=G4 A=A4 B=Bb4 c=C5 d=D5 e=E5 f=F5
%   Bass clef:   C,,=C2 D,,=D2 ... B,,=Bb2 C,=C3 D,=D3 E,=E3 F,=F3 G,=G3 A,=A3 B,=Bb3
%   Tenor (V5,V6 transpose=-12, 8vb treble): written note sounds 8va lower.
%     Written C=C4->sounds C3; D->D3; E->E3; F->F3; G->G3; A->A3; B->Bb3
%     Written c=C5->sounds C4; d->D4; e->E4; f->F4; g->G4 (T1 push max)
%
% Voice ranges used (sounding pitch):
%   S1: F4-C5 (original soprano)
%   S2: D4-A4 (third below S1, diatonic)
%   A1: C4-F4 (original alto range, melodic)
%   A2: A3-D4 (independent contra-melody, diatonic)
%   T1: C4-G4 (written c-g in 8vb treble) — comfortable to E4, push to G4 at climax
%   T2: A3-E4 (written A-e in 8vb treble) — comfortable to C4
%   Bar: E3-D4 (a third above B1, diatonic)
%   B1: F2-F3 (original bass)
%
% No accidentals in original soprano — entirely diatonic to F major.
% No chromatic harmonies requiring substitution.
% All 8 voices diatonic to F major throughout.
%
% ================================================================
% SECTION A — "Of the Father's love begotten"  (mm. 1-7)
% ================================================================
%
% mm. 1-3: Opening phrase
% Texture: S1+S2 carry melody; A1+A2 independent inner lines;
%          T1+T2 sustained fifths; Bar+B1 bass foundation.
% (4-6 voice texture at opening; builds to full 8 by m.5)
%
[V:1] [Q:1/4=108] F3/2 G/ A B A G | (A3/2 G/) F4 | A B c d (c A3/2)
[V:2]              D3/2 E/ F G F E | (F3/2 E/) D4 | F G A B (A F3/2)
[V:3]              C3/2 C/ F F F E | F2 F4        | C D F F (E C3/2)
[V:4]              A,3/2 B,/ C C C B, | C2 A,4   | A, B, C D (C A,3/2)
[V:5]              e3/2 d/ c d e e   | d2 c4      | e d c d (e c3/2)
[V:6]              c3/2 B/ A B c c   | B2 A4      | c B A B (c A3/2)
[V:7]              A,3/2 A,/ F, G, F, G, | (F,3/2 E,/) F,4 | F, G, A, B, (A, F,3/2)
[V:8]              F,3/2 F,/ F, B,, C, C, | F,2 F,4 | F, D, C, B,, (C, F,3/2)
%
% mm. 4-7: "ere the worlds began to be"
% Texture: full 8-voice homophony (gradual full texture arrival)
%
[V:1] B/ | c4 | d3/2 e/ f c c B | (A3/2 G/) F4 |
[V:2] G/ | A4 | B3/2 c/ d A A G | (F3/2 E/) D4 |
[V:3] F/ | E4 | G3/2 G/ F F F F | (F3/2 E/) F4 |
[V:4] D/ | C4 | G,3/2 G,/ A, A, B, B, | C2 A,4 |
[V:5] d/ | e4 | g3/2 g/ f e e d | (e3/2 d/) c4 |
[V:6] B/ | c4 | d3/2 d/ c c c B | (c3/2 B/) A4 |
[V:7] D,/ | C,4 | G,3/2 G,/ A, A, B, B, | C,2 C,4 |
[V:8] D,/ | C,4 | G,3/2 G,/ A, A, B, B, | C,2 F,4 |
