%
% ================================================================
% SECTION C — "Of the things that are, that have been, and that future years shall see"  (mm. 14-17)
% ================================================================
%
% mm. 14-15: "Of the things that are, that have been"
% Texture: S1+B1 outer voice dialogue; inner voices provide support
%
[V:1] (c F3/2) E/ D E | (F3/2 D/ C2) z2 |
[V:2] (A C3/2) C/ B, C | (D3/2 B,/ A,2) z2 |
[V:3] (E C3/2) D/ E D | (E3/2 C/ C2) z2 |
[V:4] (C F,3/2) C/ D C | (D3/2 B,/ F,2) z2 |
[V:5] (e c3/2) B/ A B | (c3/2 A/ G2) z2 |
[V:6] (c A3/2) G/ F G | (A3/2 F/ E2) z2 |
[V:7] (C, A,3/2) G,/ B, C, | (D,3/2 B,/ A,2) z2 |
[V:8] (F, D,3/2) C,/ B,, C, | (D,3/2 B,,/ F,2) z2 |
%
% Range checks:
%   V4 m.15: B, = Bb3 — within A2 range D3-B4. OK.
%   V8 m.14: B,, = Bb2 — within B1 range C2-A3. OK.
%   V8 m.15: B,, = Bb2 — same. OK. D, = D3. OK.
%   V7 m.15: B, = Bb3 — within Bar range E2-C4. OK. D, = D3. OK.
%
% mm. 16-17: "And that future years shall see" — climax + final cadence
% Texture: full 8-voice homophony. S1 reaches c (C5). B1 on F2 at cadence.
% A1 (V3) 4-3 suspension: E4 delays to F4 on final chord.
%
[V:1] F3/2 G/ A c A F | (G2 F4) |]
[V:2] D3/2 E/ F A F D | (E2 D4) |]
[V:3] C3/2 E/ F F F F | (E2 F4) |]
[V:4] A,3/2 C/ C C C B, | (C2 A,4) |]
[V:5] f3/2 g/ f e f f | (g2 f4) |]
[V:6] d3/2 e/ d c d d | (e2 d4) |]
[V:7] A,3/2 C/ A, A, A, D, | (C,2 A,4) |]
[V:8] F,3/2 C,/ F, A, F, D, | (C,2 F,4) |]
%
% Final cadence analysis (m.17, sustained G2→F major chord):
%   S1=F4, S2=D4, A1=F4 (resolved from E4), A2=A3(written A,),
%   T1=F4(sounding, written f), T2=D4(sounding, written d),
%   Bar=A3(written A,), B1=F2(written F,)
%   Full F major tonic chord with octave doubling. Root F in all octaves.
%
W:6.He is here, Whom seers in old time Chanted of, while ages ran;
W:Whom the writings of the prophets Promised since the world began:
W:Then foretold, now manifested, to receive the praise of man,
W:Evermore and evermore!
W:
W:7.Righteous Judge of souls departed, Righteous King of them that live,
W:On the Father's throne exalted None in might with Thee may strive;
W:Who at last in vengeance coming Sinners from Thy face shalt drive,
W:Evermore and evermore!
W:
W:8.Thee let old men, Thee let young men, Thee let choirs of infants sing;
W:Thee the matrons and the virgins, And the children answering:
W:Let their guileless songs re-echo, And the heart its music bring,
W:Evermore and evermore!
W:
W:9.Christ, to Thee with God the Father, And, O Holy Ghost, to Thee,
W:Hymn and chant with high thanksgiving, And unwearied praises be:
W:Honor, glory, and dominion, And eternal victory,
W:Evermore and evermore!
